      • FormingPattern

        public static java.lang.String FormingPattern(java.lang.String firstWord,
                                              java.lang.String secondWord)
        This function returne for a pair of input words a formation pattern specifying how the second word can be constructed via application to some transformations on the frist input word.
        Parameters:
        firstWord - first input word
        secondWord - second input word
        Returns:
        a formation pattern specifying ho the second word can be constructed from the first one or null if no pattern was found. Formation pattern syntax: "+0" - words are identical "+1" - second word is just a downcased version of the first word "+11" - second word is just a downcased version of the first word + whitespaces are replaced by underscore symbol "+2" - second word is just an uppercased version of first word "+3" - second word is obtained by trimming first word and uppercasing it "+4sl" - second word is some part of the first word, s - start, l - length "+5" - second word is normalized version of the first word "+51" - second word is normalized version of the first word and trimmed "+6" - second word is normalized version of the first word and uppercased "+61" - second word is normalized version of the first word and uppercased and trimmed "+62" - second word is normalized version of the first word and uppercased and reversed "+63" - second word is normalized version of the first word and uppercased and permuted If a pattern is followed by "+xy" - add an initial symbol x and trailing symbol y. See code comments in code for more details.

      • reverseMultiWord

        public static java.lang.String reverseMultiWord(java.lang.String word,
                                                java.lang.String delimSymbols)
        This function reverses order of words in a given multi-token word based on a given list of delimiters. Delimiters are included in the reversed word. Example: input: New York output: York New Example: input: Abc Def-GHi output: GHi-Def Abc (with 'space' and '-' as delimiters)
        Parameters:
        word - multi-token input word
        delimSymbols - a string encoding delimiter symbols
        Returns:
        a reversed version of the multi-token input word (i.e., the order of tokens is reversed)

      • permuteMultiWordAndTrim

        public static java.lang.String permuteMultiWordAndTrim(java.lang.String S,
                                                       java.lang.String delimSymbols)
        This function perform following permutation on a given multi word consisting of at least two words: input: w(1) w(2) w(3) .... w(k) output: w(2) w(3) ... w(k) w(1) A list of delimiters specifies how the multi word is segmented. Delimiters are not included in the permuted word, but a space will be inserted before last word. Example: input: Abc Def-GHi output: DefGhi Abc (with 'space' and '-' as delimiters)
        Parameters:
        S - input multi word
        delimSymbols - a string encoding delimiter symbols
        Returns:
        a permuted version of the input multi-token word, where the first token is moved to trhe last position
